  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I had never done any physics or chemistry or biology.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I had a very strange education.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't think I spent more than a year in school in five years.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But when I went to the school at Porto San Giorgio, I went into the top class before O level and somehow managed it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I got my equivalent-- it was called [NON-ENGLISH], lower matriculation in Polish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "During the Easter holidays, I was sent to a recuperation center on Lake Como, because I wasn't very strong at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And in August '45, the whole school and some of the other units left Italy as part of army repatriation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we came to England, landed at Liverpool, traveled on the a splendid ship, arrived in Liverpool at the end of August-- rain, cold, miserable.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We went to a camp in West Kirby, from where we were transferred to another camp near Hereford at Foxley.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And my parents were still in Italy at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But my father's brother, the journalist, was a member of the editorial team of the Polish newspaper in England, That he and his wife and son, who was born in 1944, were living in London.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I came to see them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And very soon, I decided that I really wanted to go to an English school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If we were going to stay in England, there was no point in staying in the Polish school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So when my parents arrived in England in October, I put it to them that I thought it was time I moved on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] my mother's brother, with his wife and son, who before the war lived in Belgium, were also in London.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
